The paper proposes a technique for initializing weights in a single layer feedforward neural network and applies it to a modified gated recurrent encoder-decoder network for short-term load forecasting. This involves machine learning techniques such as RNN and seq2seq networks, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). The application of the proposed technique to a real-world problem in the energy market also suggests relevance to the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
